  "prompt": "Is there a way that I can customize the window background color before a page loads?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several ways to customize the window or page background color before a page loads:\n\n1. CSS Background Color (Recommended):\n```css\nbody {\n    background-color: #your-color-here;\n}\n```\n\n2. Meta Tag for Mobile (Specific browsers):\n```html\n<meta name=\"theme-color\" content=\"#your-color-here\">\n```\n\n3. Inline Style:\n```html\n<body style=\"background-color: #your-color-here;\">\n```\n\n4. JavaScript (Dynamic):\n```javascript\ndocument.body.style.backgroundColor = '#your-color-here';\n```\n\n5. For Single Page Applications, you can set it in the index.html:\n```html\n<html style=\"background-color: #your-color-here;\">\n```\n\n6. CSS with Preload:\n```css\nhtml, body {\n    background-color: #your-color-here;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 0;\n}\n```\n\nChoose the method that best fits your specific use case and application structure.",
